article.headline: Belmont 106, Fisk 49
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Andrew House made 9-of-12 floor shots and scored 23 points to lead Belmont past crosstown rival Fisk 106-49 Tuesday. Belmont (6-3) got points from 11 of its 12 players, including six in double figures. Mike Dejworek and Shane Dansby scored 12 each, Andy Wicke and Justin Hare had 11 each and Jordan Campbell 10. Fisk (1-6), which trailed 49-21 at halftime, was led by Aaron Hamilton with 23 points and Thurloo Pearson with 13. Belmont shot 59.2 percent from the floor to 33.9 percent for Fisk. Only four Fisk players scored.
